song_name: We Might Be Dead By Tomorrow
We Might Be Dead By Tomorrow

version_description: It's easiest to play with a capo on the 3rd fret. Otherwise you can skip it and transpose up 3 halfsteps. I've previously published the chords to a live version, but this is more thorough and accurate.
This version has detailed chord progression and how to play it accordingly. Might have been more sophisticated but it sounds truer to my ears. I hope it sounds true to yours too.
This is an acoustic version instead of the full electric.
From the new album "Prequelle". Capo on 1st fret, or skip it and transpose up 1 half step.
Capo on 3rd fret, or skip it and transpose up 3 half steps.
Basic chord progression of the song.
Ghost tunes down to D and plays it in E, but this works better for an acoustic. The original solo has some other parts, but this'll do fine.
This version is the only full version on the site, with actual chords for the chorus and a way to play it acoustically.
This is just a version with the chords that can be played with no capo. I'd recommend playing the chords in the verses up on the eighth fret as that fits the song better.
Capo makes it easier to hold the D# chord, which is a A# chord with the capo. The chords are set in root note with the main key of the song, which is Dm, or a Am with the capo on.
